            <b>Location:</b> In the northern suburbs of Wellington to the east a few blocks from the northern motorway (SH1) 10km from the ferry terminals, 15mins Normal traffic 30mins Peak hour. Detailed maps are part of your booking confirmation messages sent via email and text.<br />
            <b>Access: </b>The site is flat with easy access from the street, able to park either front or rear facing. It's 8 x 3.9-4.0 meters, room for most RVs even with Slide-Out. There is on street parking for anything you might be towing, a 5th wheel rig, or if you have a caravan.<br />
            <b>Power: </b>The external power to a 16A caravan socket from a protected 16amp outlet It is very close to the pad.<br />
            <b>Internet:</b> We have good WIFI available in this location, fed from fibre, you should have no speed wobbles.<br />
            <b>Tap water: </b>A tap is on the parking pad to replenish your potable water tanks.<br />
            <b>Grey Water Waste:</b> We have a gully trap on the parking pad suitable for disposing of your grey water waste.>
